4 A JOINT RESOLUTION OF THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
5 MONTANA TO RELEASE CERTAIN WILDERNESS STUDY AREAS IN MONTANA FROM CONSIDERATION
6 FOR INCLUSION IN THE NATIONAL WILDERNESS PRESERVATION SYSTEM.
7
8 WHEREAS, Congress has passed the Federal Land Policy and Management Act of 1976 and the
9 Montana Wilderness Study Act of 1977; and
10 WHEREAS, the Montana Wilderness Study Act required the Secretary of Agriculture to review certain
11 lands within 5 years to determine suitability for preservation as wilderness and report the findings to the
12 President; and
13 WHEREAS, the Federal Land Policy and Management Act defines the management responsibilities of
14 the Bureau of Land Management, including land inventories and land-use plans; and
15 WHEREAS, the Roadless Area Conservation Rule was published in 2001, directing the U.S. Forest
16 Service to inventory roadless areas, generally limiting timber harvest, road construction and reconstruction; and
17 WHEREAS, almost 663,000 acres of land in Montana are designated under the Montana Wilderness
18 Study Act, including:
19 (1) West Pioneer Wilderness Study Area comprising approximately 151,000 acres;
20 (2) Blue Joint Wilderness Study Area comprising approximately 61,000 acres;
21 (3) Sapphire Wilderness Study Area comprising approximately 94,000 acres;
22 (4) Ten Lakes Wilderness Study Area comprising approximately 34,000 acres;
23 (5) Middle Fork Judith Wilderness Study Area comprising approximately 81,000 acres;
24 (6) Big Snowies Wilderness Study Area comprising approximately 91,000 acres; and
25 (7) Hyalite-Porcupine-Buffalo Horn Wilderness Study Area comprising approximately 151,000
26 acres; and
27 WHEREAS, the 5-year period for review mandated by the Montana Wilderness Study Act expired in
28 1982; and
