1 mandate as required by the Organic Act of 1897 to manage the national forests to "improve and protect the
2 forest within the reservation, or for the purpose of securing favorable conditions of water flows, and to furnish a
3 continuous supply of timber for the use and necessities of citizens of the United States".
4 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that in its deliberations, Congress consider the land management
5 alternatives in view of the Organic Act of 1897 in conjunction with the 2007 water rights compact between the
6 state of Montana and the U.S. Department of Agriculture Forest Service, since land management directly
7 impacts the volume, quantity, and timing of water flows from watersheds in these wilderness study areas and
8 impacts downstream water rights holders.
9 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Legislature urges the Secretary of the Department of
10 Agriculture to direct the Forest Service to immediately evaluate the impacts of the land management
11 alternatives on the watersheds in the Montana wilderness study areas and downstream water rights holders to
12 help inform Congress in its deliberations.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Legislature urges the Secretary of the Department of the
14 Interior to direct the Bureau of Land Management to immediately evaluate the impacts of the land management
15 alternatives on the watersheds in the Montana wilderness study areas and downstream water rights holders to
16 help inform Congress in its deliberations.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Secretary of State send copies of this resolution to the
18 Governor, the Montana Congressional Delegation, the United States Secretary of the Interior, the United States
19 Secretary of Agriculture, the Chief of the Forest Service, and the Director of the Bureau of Land Management.
